This paper deals with few-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to improve classification performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new learning paradigm, which involves the use of class concepts, and discusses the use of label information to refine image representations, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of state-of-the-art models, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
